  <slide>
    <title>Importance of skip links</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li>Reduces tabbing for keyboard only users to get over repetitive links at the beginning of pages to get to the main content.</li>
        <li>Not important to screeen reader users when headings and landmarks are available on the page.</li>
        <li>Primary benefit is for keyboard only users who are not using assisitve technology.</li>
        <li>Main stream browsers will not implement native structural navigation support.</li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <style>
      dt { font-weight: bold; padding-top: 1em;}
